<subSubSection id="57C1ECB0FFEFD618CBF7BEE70534F441" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="1F64BF3BFFEFD618CBF7BEE70534F441" blockId="4.[151,1436,1478,2007]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="D8DBC4B8FFEFD618CA71BEE70628F6D8" authority="Levinsen, 1878" authorityName="Levinsen" authorityYear="1878" box="[273,580,1478,1503]" class="Hexanauplia" family="Bradophilidae" genus="Bradophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2DAF6329FFEFD618CA71BEE705FDF6D8" box="[273,401,1478,1503]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Bradophila</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="7B4AC2CAFFEFD618CAF8BEE70628F6D8" author="Levinsen, G. M. R." box="[408,580,1478,1503]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="351 - 380" refId="ref47405" refString="Levinsen, G. M. R. (1878) Om nogle parasitiske Krebsdyr, der snylte hos Annelider. Fidenskalbelige Meddelelser fra dansk Naturhistorisk Forening I KJObenhavn, 1877 - 78, 351 - 380, pl. 6." type="journal article" year="1878">Levinsen, 1878</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described by 
<bibRefCitation id="7B4AC2CAFFEFD618C8E6BEE70052F6D8" author="Levinsen, G. M. R." box="[902,1086,1478,1503]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="351 - 380" refId="ref47405" refString="Levinsen, G. M. R. (1878) Om nogle parasitiske Krebsdyr, der snylte hos Annelider. Fidenskalbelige Meddelelser fra dansk Naturhistorisk Forening I KJObenhavn, 1877 - 78, 351 - 380, pl. 6." type="journal article" year="1878">Levinsen (1878)</bibRefCitation>
but over 120 years later, it was 
<bibRefCitation id="7B4AC2CAFFEFD618CBF7BECB051BF504" author="Marchenkov, A. V." box="[151,375,1514,1539]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" refId="ref47852" refString="Marchenkov, A. V. (1999) Symbiotic and parasitic Crustacea off benthic marine invertebrates from the Arctic Seas of Russia. Unpublished PhD thesis, Zoological Institute, Russian Academy of Sciences, Saint Petersburg, 193 pp." type="book" year="1999">Marchenkov (1999)</bibRefCitation>
who first suggested that it belonged in a separate family and later he formally established the family (
<bibRefCitation id="7B4AC2CAFFEFD618CB90BD2F05A9F520" author="Marchenkov, A. V." box="[240,453,1550,1575]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="514 - 516" refId="ref47894" refString="Marchenkov, A. V. (2002) Bradophilidae fam. nov. - the new family of mesoparasitic copepod collected from the polychaete Brada villosa from the White Sea. Parazitologiya, 36 (6), 514 - 516." type="journal article" year="2002">Marchenkov 2002</bibRefCitation>
). The genus and family have remained monotypic until recently, although 
<bibRefCitation id="7B4AC2CAFFEFD618CE7ABD2F0556F54C" author="Boxshall, G. A. &amp; Halsey, S. H." pageId="4" pageNumber="5" refId="ref45773" refString="Boxshall, G. A. &amp; Halsey, S. H. (2004) An Introduction to Copepod Diversity. The Ray Society, London, 966 pp." type="book" year="2004">Boxshall &amp; Halsey (2004)</bibRefCitation>
suggested a possible relationship with the poorly known 
<taxonomicName id="D8DBC4B8FFEFD618C882BD1301F4F54C" authority="M'Intosh, 1885" authorityName="M'Intosh" authorityYear="1885" box="[994,1432,1586,1611]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Bradophilidae" genus="Trophonophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bradii">
<emphasis id="2DAF6329FFEFD618C882BD1300B4F54C" box="[994,1240,1586,1611]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Trophonophila bradii</emphasis>
M’Intosh, 1885
</taxonomicName>
, which also occurs on a flabelligerid polychaete host, taken in deep water to the south of 
<collectingCountry id="67CCFFABFFEFD618CF0EBD7700B9F568" box="[1134,1237,1622,1647]" name="Australia" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Australia</collectingCountry>
(M’Intosh 1885). 
<bibRefCitation id="7B4AC2CAFFEFD618CBF7BD5A0544F594" author="Huys, R." box="[151,296,1658,1683]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="355 - 385" refId="ref47088" refString="Huys, R. (2016) Enigmas from the past: M'Intosh's (1885) annelidicolous copepods from the voyage of H. M. S. Challenger. Zootaxa, 4174 (1), 355 - 385. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4174.1.22" type="journal article" year="2016">Huys (2016)</bibRefCitation>
re-examined the 
<typeStatus id="C0600199FFEFD618CA99BD5B0637F594" box="[505,603,1658,1683]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">holotype</typeStatus>
female of 
<taxonomicName id="D8DBC4B8FFEFD618C981BD5D0729F594" authorityName="M'Intosh" authorityYear="1885" box="[737,837,1658,1683]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Bradophilidae" genus="Trophonophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bradii">
<emphasis id="2DAF6329FFEFD618C981BD5D0729F594" box="[737,837,1658,1683]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">T. bradii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and confirmed that this genus is a member of the 
<taxonomicName id="D8DBC4B8FFEFD618CBF7BDBF0556F5B0" authorityName="Marchenkov" authorityYear="2002" box="[151,314,1694,1719]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Bradophilidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Bradophilidae</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="7B4AC2CAFFEFD618CA29BDBE05B7F5B0" author="Huys, R." box="[329,475,1694,1719]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="355 - 385" refId="ref47088" refString="Huys, R. (2016) Enigmas from the past: M'Intosh's (1885) annelidicolous copepods from the voyage of H. M. S. Challenger. Zootaxa, 4174 (1), 355 - 385. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4174.1.22" type="journal article" year="2016">Huys (2016)</bibRefCitation>
also considered that the name of the species should be changed to 
<taxonomicName id="D8DBC4B8FFEFD618CE6EBDBE0114F5B0" box="[1294,1400,1694,1719]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Bradophilidae" genus="Trophonophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bradyi">
<emphasis id="2DAF6329FFEFD618CE6EBDBE0114F5B0" box="[1294,1400,1694,1719]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">T. bradyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as M’Intosh (1885) explicitly named the species after George Stewardson Brady. However, since the original spelling given by M’Intosh (
<taxonomicName id="D8DBC4B8FFEFD618CA18BDC705D0F5F8" authorityName="M'Intosh" authorityYear="1885" box="[376,444,1766,1791]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Bradophilidae" genus="Trophonophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bradii">
<emphasis id="2DAF6329FFEFD618CA18BDC705D0F5F8" box="[376,444,1766,1791]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">bradii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) clearly constitutes an attempt at the latinization of Brady’s name, we retain the original spelling in accord with ICZN Art. 32.5.1, which states that incorrect latinization is not to be considered an inadvertent error.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="57C1ECB0FFEFD619CBA7BC730606F21B" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="description">
<paragraph id="1F64BF3BFFEFD619CBA7BC730606F21B" blockId="4.[151,1436,1478,2007]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
The globular and limbless ectosoma of adult female 
<taxonomicName id="D8DBC4B8FFEFD618C85CBC7307D0F46C" authorityName="Levinsen" authorityYear="1878" box="[828,956,1874,1899]" class="Hexanauplia" family="Bradophilidae" genus="Bradophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2DAF6329FFEFD618C85CBC7307D0F46C" box="[828,956,1874,1899]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Bradophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles that of females of the family 
<taxonomicName id="D8DBC4B8FFEFD618CBF7BC57052EF488" authorityName="Hansen" authorityYear="1892" box="[151,322,1910,1935]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Herpyllobiidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Herpyllobiidae</taxonomicName>
, but these two families differ markedly in the structure of the males: 
<taxonomicName id="D8DBC4B8FFEFD618CF34BC5700BFF488" authorityName="Levinsen" authorityYear="1878" box="[1108,1235,1910,1935]" class="Hexanauplia" family="Bradophilidae" genus="Bradophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2DAF6329FFEFD618CF34BC5700BFF488" box="[1108,1235,1910,1935]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Bradophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
males have welldeveloped, prehensile antennae which are used to attach to the ectosoma of the female, plus recognizable antennules, mandibles, maxillules, maxillae, and maxillipeds (
<bibRefCitation id="7B4AC2CAFFEFD618C801BC9F0059F4D0" author="Marchenkov, A. V." box="[865,1077,1982,2007]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="514 - 516" refId="ref47894" refString="Marchenkov, A. V. (2002) Bradophilidae fam. nov. - the new family of mesoparasitic copepod collected from the polychaete Brada villosa from the White Sea. Parazitologiya, 36 (6), 514 - 516." type="journal article" year="2002">Marchenkov 2002</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="7B4AC2CAFFEFD618CF24BC9E00AAF4D0" author="Huys, R." box="[1092,1222,1982,2007]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="355 - 385" refId="ref47088" refString="Huys, R. (2016) Enigmas from the past: M'Intosh's (1885) annelidicolous copepods from the voyage of H. M. S. Challenger. Zootaxa, 4174 (1), 355 - 385. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4174.1.22" type="journal article" year="2016">Huys 2016</bibRefCitation>
). In contrast, male herpyllobiids lack all cephalothoracic appendages except for males of 
<taxonomicName id="D8DBC4B8FFEED619C8A0BBB60550F3D2" authority="Lopez-Gonzalez, Bresciani &amp; Conradi, 2006" authorityName="Lopez-Gonzalez, Bresciani &amp; Conradi" authorityYear="2006" class="Maxillopoda" family="Herpyllobiidae" genus="Gottoniella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2DAF6329FFEED619C8A0BBB6002CF3B7" box="[960,1088,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Gottoniella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="7B4AC2CAFFEED619CF29BBB60550F3D2" author="Lopez-Gonzalez, P. J. &amp; Bresciani, J. &amp; Conradi, M." pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="243 - 259" refId="ref47580" refString="Lopez-Gonzalez, P. J., Bresciani, J. &amp; Conradi, M. (2006) New genus, three new species and new records of Herpyllobiidae Hansen, 1892 (Crustacea, Copepoda), parasites of polychaetes from Antarctica. Scientia Marina, 70, 243 - 259. https: // doi. org / 10.3989 / scimar. 2006.70 n 2243." type="journal article" year="2006">López-González, Bresciani &amp; Conradi, 2006</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which possess a pair of 3-segmented subchelate limbs, identified as probably the maxillipeds by 
<bibRefCitation id="7B4AC2CAFFEED619CBF7BBFE058FF3FF" author="Lopez-Gonzalez, P. J. &amp; Bresciani, J. &amp; Conradi, M." box="[151,483,223,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="243 - 259" refId="ref47580" refString="Lopez-Gonzalez, P. J., Bresciani, J. &amp; Conradi, M. (2006) New genus, three new species and new records of Herpyllobiidae Hansen, 1892 (Crustacea, Copepoda), parasites of polychaetes from Antarctica. Scientia Marina, 70, 243 - 259. https: // doi. org / 10.3989 / scimar. 2006.70 n 2243." type="journal article" year="2006">
López-González 
<emphasis id="2DAF6329FFEED619CA37BBC005E3F3FF" box="[343,399,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">et al.</emphasis>
(2006)
</bibRefCitation>
, and males of 
<taxonomicName id="D8DBC4B8FFEED619C9E4BBFE0775F3FF" authorityName="M. Sars" authorityYear="1870" box="[644,793,223,248]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Herpyllobiidae" genus="Eurysilenium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2DAF6329FFEED619C9E4BBFE0775F3FF" box="[644,793,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Eurysilenium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which possess a pair of stylet-like structures of uncertain affinity in the oral region (
<bibRefCitation id="7B4AC2CAFFEED619CAA0BA240636F21A" author="Lutzen, J." box="[448,602,260,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="241 - 274" refId="ref47649" refString="Lutzen, J. (1964 a) A revision of the family Herpyllobiidae, (parasitic copepods) with notes on hosts and distribution. Ophelia, 1, 241 - 274. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00785326.1964.10416282" type="journal article" year="1964">Lützen 1964a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
